
Common keyboard shortcuts:

  Text commands (such as cut and paste)
  operate on the text where the cursor is
  located text rather than the main window.

  ctrl+a       Select all
  ctrl+c       Copy
  ctrl+l       Select current line (subsequent select next line)
  ctrl+q       Quit (exit editor)
  crtl+w       Close buffer
  ctrl+s       Save file
  ctrl+v       Paste
  ctrl+x       Cut
  ctrl+y       Redo
  ctrl+z       Undo
  esc          Return to the main window


Within the main text window:

  ctrl+f       Find
  ctrl+g       Go to line
  ctrl+r       Reverse find


Within Find:

  return       Return to main window
  esc          Return to main window
  ctrl+f       Find next
  ctrl+g       Find next
  ctrl+r       Reverse find


Within Goto:

  return       Go to the line, column specified
  esc          Return to main window
  t            Jump to top of buffer
  h            Jump to halfway point of buffer
  b            Jump to bottom of buffer
